Ephesians 1:7

Context : 
The Apostle Paul is speaking to the Ephesian people.
Paul is talking about our redemption of your sins through Jesus Christ.

Paraphrase : 
Through the power of the blood of Christ, we are redeemed and are forgiven for our sins, according to the riches of his grace.

Reflection :
I am a sinner and the only way to salvation is though the grace of God through Christ.
Because of his Grace and love for me, I am redeemed though his Blood and his sacrifice.